V. CONCLUSION
In conclusion, we have shown that the general shape equation when specialized to an axisymmetric membrane is identical to the shape equation which is obtained if axisymmetry is assumed in the first place. However, the latter method requires the proper inclusion of Lagrange multipliers and the correct treatment of boundary terms. For vesicles of spherical topology a simplification occurs. Once this simplification has been introduced, all subsequent results hold only for spherical topology.

